{
  "texts": [
    "Ultimately, the trust will be able to select the majority of board members (Fig. 3).External ethics boards have a number of advantages.",
    "First, they can legally bind the company through the contractual relationship (Sect. 5.2).",
    "This would be much more difficult for internal structures (Sect. 3.2).",
    "Second, the board would be more independent, mainly because it would be less affected by internal incentives (e.g.",
    "board members could prioritize the public interest over the company's interests)."
  ]
}